#1st day i learn about HTML TUTORIAL FOR BEGINNERS 

1.what is html
*html=hyper text markup language
*used to structure web pages
*uses tags to tell the browser what each part is



2.basic html document structure
 <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
 <head>
   <title>my first page</tittle>
 </head>
<body>
  <h1>hello world</h1>
  <p>this is my first website.</p>
</body>
</html>

3.explanation
<!DOCTYPE html>
Tells the browser this is an HTML5 document

<html>
Root element

All HTML code goes inside this tag
<head>
Contains meta information
Not shown on the page

Includes:

<title> (page name in browser tab)
<meta> (charset, viewport, SEO info)
<link> (CSS)
<script> (JS)
<title>
Shows text on the browser tab
<body>
Contains visible content
Headings, paragraphs, images, links, buttons, etc

4.most common html tags inside <body>
*<h1> to<h6>  -> headings
*<p>->paragraph
*<a>->link 
*<img>->image
*<br> → line break
*<hr> → horizontal line

5.html rules
Most tags have opening and closing tags
<p>Text</p>
Tags are nested properly
HTML is not case-sensitive, but lowercase is best practice


6.File Rules
Save file as: index.html
Open in any browser (Chrome, Edge, Firefox)



7. HTML = structure, not design
(CSS = design, JavaScript = behavior)

#summary 
*html uses tags <> </> to present  content
*there are many different tags
*tags can contain attributes <p class="my class">
*tags can be nested in other tags
*tags are normally indented when nested for readability
